{"author":{"id":"8e1777f58c0cfe5478428be8f9fcbfe90d25e44689578335da8fc2246fe0915a"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1603273151,"nonce":"hX4+RzkKZHIe8nkGXmDDQ/OLHwI=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWU3MjYzMTI4MDU=","github-url":"https://github.com/galaxyproject/tools-iuc/issues/3260","origin":"github"},"title":"add KofamScan to IUC","message":"-----------\nI was wondering if it would be possible to include this new annotation tool from KEGG into Galaxy.\n\nhttps://www.genome.jp/tools/kofamkoala/ \n\nThere is a small program KofamScan (uses HMMER \u0026 Ruby) to simplify the job. The K-number hmms are downloaded as a database and one uses simple text files to select which subsets of K-numbers to search against.\n\nI think this would complement the InterProScan annotations very well as only ECs are given by InterProScan and not K-numbers; the latter being more specific.\n----------------------","files":null}]}